restoration and recognition

02:19:09.930 --> 02:19:13.299
of our tribes' inherent
sovereignty to protect tribal

02:19:13.299 --> 02:19:15.620
citizens and including
its own Native women,

02:19:15.620 --> 02:19:18.000
when that legal
framework shifts,

02:19:18.000 --> 02:19:21.129
I think we'll see either
as a result of or as a part

02:19:21.129 --> 02:19:23.930
of, or maybe the
driving force will be,

02:19:23.930 --> 02:19:26.309
a cultural shift the United
States where women go from

02:19:26.309 --> 02:19:29.670
being sexual objects to be
abused to being actual citizens

02:19:29.670 --> 02:19:31.340
to be respected.

02:19:31.340 --> 02:19:37.860
And I think when you look at a
lot of the way our Native women

02:19:37.860 --> 02:19:40.354
are depicted in American
culture, I mean,

02:19:40.354 --> 02:19:43.020
they're just a Halloween costume
right now in the United States.

02:19:43.020 --> 02:19:43.730
Literally.

02:19:43.730 --> 02:19:50.250
Or maybe really like
a Pocahontas kind

02:19:50.250 --> 02:19:51.710
